This paper focuses on improving the visual quality of super-resolved images using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) is also mentioned, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of multi-scale hierarchical features fusion, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
